AFTER more than three decades of running The Coliseum and five years after shutting down, Ken Caleb-Olumese is finally letting go of the iconic Niteshift Coliseum. According to information gathered by The Nation, Olumese has not put The Coliseum up for sale but has finally agreed to a lease plan for his premium nightclub sitting on a sprawling over 1,900 square metres in the Opebi area of Ikeja, Lagos.   Zee One to celebrate 2022 Valentine with Bollywood love…     Aso believes working hard will leave huge legacy in the…     Netflix eyes King Of Boys’ editor Steve Sodiya   A source hinted that Olumese has signed a multi-million naira lease agreement with nightlife entrepreneur, Kola Eddo and his partner to run The Coliseum. While the terms of the lease deal has been kept secret, the source said it’s a long term, mouth-watering lease agreement that fits into Olumese’s dream and plan for the structure. Already, minor renovation has commenced with little touch on the exterior of the well-maintained hangout.